obo:ECO_0006042  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4586  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: - Arginine methylation is a major PTM that regulates chromatin structure, transcription, and splicing within the nucleus.\n\n- Figure 1G: Western blot shows upregulated protein arginine methyltransferase PRMT8 expression in the hippocampus when dendritic spine maturation occurs.\n- Figure 2: Depletion of PRMT8 by shRNA knockdown leads to overabundance of filopodia and mislocalization of excitatory synapses.\n- Figure 4B-D: spine morphology alterations can also be found in hippocampi of PTM8 KO mice.\n- Figure 5-6 : Spinning disc, confocal microscopy, FRAP assays and Western blots show that PRMT8 promotes dendritic spine morphology through methylation of the dendritic RNA-binding protein G3BP1 and suppression of the Rac1-PAK1 signaling pathway to control synaptic actin dynamics.. Experimental description: Mouse and rat species are both used throughout figures related to this annotation, we annotate against mouse species based on Figures 4-6 which are central to this annotation (but the same annotation would apply to the respective rat protein).\n\n- Primary hippocampal neurons were cultured from Prmt8 knockout mice Prmt8tm1a(EUCOMM)\n- Antibody:Rabbit polyclonal anti-PRMT8 (ICC) Thermo Fisher Scientific (discontinued) Cat#PA5-19846; RRID: AB_10985902\n- For making FLAG-tagged PRMT8, the PRMT8 insert was amplified from synthetic full length human PRMT8, the PCR product was digested by EcoRI and KpnI and sub-cloned into the pEGFP-N1 vector." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-01-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4586" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

